        <!-- ABOUT HEADING -->
        <h1>
          About <br />St. Columbus Public School
        </h1>
        <div class="paragraph-container">
          <p>
            St. Columbus Public School, established in 2002 at Ekdara, Jhajha
            (Jamui, Bihar), is a co-educational English-medium school dedicated
            to providing quality education with strong values. It is recognized
            for its disciplined environment, caring teachers, and focus on
            building a solid academic foundation for students. <br /><br />
            The school provides unique features such as a well-structured
            curriculum, a focus on developing independent thinking, and
            opportunities for academic, physical, and moral growth. Students
            benefit from a dedicated library that encourages reading and
            exploration beyond textbooks, along with a playground for games and
            physical activities that build teamwork, fitness, and confidence.
            The school emphasizes discipline, strong moral values, and
            co-curricular activities, helping students grow into responsible,
            well-rounded individuals.
            <br />
            The campus is designed to provide a safe, supportive, and peaceful
            learning environment away from the distractions of city life. St.
            Columbus Public School encourages students to explore their talents
            and interests while fostering confidence, curiosity, and respect for
            society. With caring teachers and staff providing guidance and
            attention to each student, the school ensures that children not only
            excel academically but also develop essential life skills and values
            for long-term success.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

